  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Always include a <a href="/docs/elements/native/caption/"><code>&lt;caption&gt;</code></a>:</strong> provides context for screen reader users navigating to the table</li>
      <li><strong>Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th&gt;</code></a> with <code>scope</code>:</strong> define whether headers apply to columns (<code>scope="col"</code>) or rows (<code>scope="row"</code>)</li>
      <li><strong>Structure with <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a>:</strong> helps assistive technologies understand table regions</li>
      <li><strong>Avoid empty cells:</strong> use appropriate content or "N/A" rather than leaving cells blank</li>
      <li><strong>Keep tables simple:</strong> avoid complex merged cells when possible; use <code>scope="colgroup"</code> for multi-level headers</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

